WEBVTT

01:23.917 --> 01:25.377
Hi, Amanda.

01:26.461 --> 01:27.337
Good morning.

01:27.421 --> 01:28.589
- Hi.
- Hey, baby.

01:32.634 --> 01:34.970
Hey, honey, laundry's done.

01:35.762 --> 01:37.806
Amanda. No, no, no.

01:52.112 --> 01:53.822
- Let's hear it, Amanda. Come on.
- Yeah.

01:53.905 --> 01:54.905
All right.

02:12.841 --> 02:14.676
Happy birthday, Amanda.

03:50.188 --> 03:53.692
Good, good, good.
All right, good job, everybody.

03:53.775 --> 03:56.069
We'll see you tomorrow at 5 pm.

03:56.153 --> 03:58.280
So eat well, rest well.

03:58.363 --> 04:01.867
And if anyone has any problems,
don't let me know.

04:03.118 --> 04:04.870
All right, good.

04:08.206 --> 04:09.206
Amanda.

04:10.625 --> 04:12.627
- That was really good.
- Thanks.

04:33.315 --> 04:35.442
- What's up, Rick?
- Come on, guys.

04:35.525 --> 04:37.527
Oh, how's it going, man?

04:37.611 --> 04:39.279
That's a nice bag, man.

04:39.362 --> 04:41.531
- Please, stop it.
- Oh, this is nice.

04:42.199 --> 04:44.326
- Give me my bag back.
- It is pretty nice.

04:45.285 --> 04:46.828
Come on, I'm gonna be late to class.

04:48.705 --> 04:50.540
Come on, please.
Give it back. Stop, please.

05:50.767 --> 05:53.436
- Hey, honey, I'm exhausted.
- I'm gonna crash.

05:53.520 --> 05:54.938
Just call him right now.

05:58.191 --> 05:59.192
Bye-bye.

09:46.461 --> 09:48.421
Hi, I was just around the corner.

09:48.505 --> 09:51.883
I just thought
I'd bring you some supplies.

09:51.966 --> 09:54.219
Did you come to bring supplies,

09:55.261 --> 09:57.097
or to watch the concerto?

09:58.223 --> 09:59.223
Both.

10:04.521 --> 10:06.856
Some of this food's had an anniversary.

10:08.149 --> 10:10.110
Anything else you want me to bring?

10:10.193 --> 10:12.654
No, I have everything I need.

10:12.737 --> 10:13.655
Love.

10:13.738 --> 10:14.614
What?

10:14.697 --> 10:16.449
Love is all you need.

10:18.451 --> 10:21.913
What's new?
See Rob's working on his heart attack.

10:22.747 --> 10:24.374
Kate's got a new boyfriend.

10:24.457 --> 10:26.376
- Fucking hated the other one.
- Leave me alone.

10:26.459 --> 10:29.045
- Rick's still being bullied.
- Stop. Come on.

10:30.630 --> 10:32.757
Come on, please.

10:32.841 --> 10:34.509
Leave me alone. Stop.

10:40.014 --> 10:41.724
When's luiza getting married?

10:45.103 --> 10:46.104
Will?

10:46.187 --> 10:48.439
All information is in her cabinet.

10:48.523 --> 10:51.526
Yeah, I know,
but when's she getting married?

10:51.609 --> 10:53.069
In eight days.

10:53.153 --> 10:54.028
Oh, perfect.

10:54.112 --> 10:55.864
Got a window there.

10:55.947 --> 10:57.282
Thanks for the invite.

10:58.199 --> 10:59.534
Beautiful dress.

11:07.792 --> 11:09.878
Fernando's doing much better.

11:16.301 --> 11:18.511
Right, she's heading to the concerto.

11:20.597 --> 11:22.015
What time does it start?

11:23.725 --> 11:24.767
At 6.

11:28.104 --> 11:29.814
So why's she driving so fast?

12:00.136 --> 12:01.136
Will.

12:02.222 --> 12:03.223
What did you say?

12:03.973 --> 12:05.975
Have you seen anything different?

12:15.276 --> 12:16.319
Yes?

12:16.402 --> 12:18.488
She had some problems sleeping.

12:21.532 --> 12:25.245
But she always had problems sleeping
before big concertos.

12:27.914 --> 12:28.914
Well...

12:30.625 --> 12:31.625
Well...

12:33.211 --> 12:35.713
Nothing we do now
is gonna change anything.

12:50.853 --> 12:52.772
I heard her tires squeal.

13:12.000 --> 13:13.501
Try to get some rest, eh?

13:16.587 --> 13:18.798
Tomorrow you got a lot of work to do.

13:29.559 --> 13:30.935
Do you like it, Amanda?

13:46.367 --> 13:48.161
Who did you draw here, Amanda?

13:48.244 --> 13:49.537
- My friend.
- Yeah?

13:49.620 --> 13:52.206
Is this the friend that we never see?

13:52.290 --> 13:53.333
The friend again.

13:54.834 --> 13:56.753
Do you ever talk to your friend?

13:56.836 --> 13:59.714
Not really, but he's always with me.

14:01.424 --> 14:02.884
What's your friend's name?

14:02.967 --> 14:03.801
Will.

14:03.885 --> 14:04.886
His name is will.

15:09.158 --> 15:10.451
Please, come in.

15:14.122 --> 15:15.122
Thank you.

15:19.085 --> 15:21.212
My name is will, by the way.

15:23.005 --> 15:24.841
May I call you...

15:32.557 --> 15:33.557
Sure.

15:35.226 --> 15:36.644
May I take your picture?

15:37.687 --> 15:38.688
My pleasure.

15:45.236 --> 15:46.904
How old are you, Anne?

15:46.988 --> 15:47.988
Foun

15:48.364 --> 15:50.408
four minutes?

15:50.992 --> 15:51.992
Four hours.

15:52.785 --> 15:53.911
And some minutes.

15:55.580 --> 15:57.832
When did you learn how to speak?

15:57.915 --> 15:59.125
I don't know.

16:00.293 --> 16:02.378
I think I always knew how to speak.

16:02.462 --> 16:04.130
Do you know why you're here?

16:04.213 --> 16:05.298
Strangely, yes.

16:05.381 --> 16:08.968
Do you mind if I say it out loud,
just to make it official?

16:09.051 --> 16:10.051
Okay.

16:11.554 --> 16:12.972
As you know,

16:13.639 --> 16:17.810
you are being considered
for the amazing opportunity of life.

16:18.644 --> 16:21.272
If, after this process, you are selected,

16:21.355 --> 16:25.735
you will have the chance
to be born in a fruitful environment

16:25.818 --> 16:26.986
where you can grow,

16:27.069 --> 16:28.738
develop,

16:28.821 --> 16:29.822
and accomplish.

16:29.906 --> 16:32.617
Would you like
to be considered for this position?

16:32.700 --> 16:33.784
I would.

16:33.868 --> 16:36.996
Before we get started, may I call you...

16:37.079 --> 16:38.080
Mike?

16:40.166 --> 16:41.876
Alexander?

16:41.959 --> 16:42.960
Kane?

16:50.510 --> 16:52.094
Do you have any questions?

16:55.306 --> 16:57.850
- Am I dead?
- I wouldn't say you're alive or dead.

16:57.934 --> 16:59.393
Are you the boss?

16:59.477 --> 17:01.187
I would say, a cog in the wheel.

17:02.688 --> 17:03.981
That sounds intense.

17:04.065 --> 17:05.858
How long is this process?

17:05.942 --> 17:07.652
Hard to pinpoint exactly,

17:07.734 --> 17:10.238
but if you make it
until the end, nine days.

17:10.320 --> 17:12.490
- So I have nine days.
- Yes.

17:12.573 --> 17:13.449
Or less.

17:13.532 --> 17:14.532
After that?

17:14.575 --> 17:15.701
If you're selected,

17:15.785 --> 17:18.496
there is an extension as a newborn.

17:19.955 --> 17:21.958
If not, I would say it's the end.

17:22.541 --> 17:26.503
By "extension," do you mean
I carry on the memories from here?

17:26.587 --> 17:28.881
No. No memories.

17:29.924 --> 17:31.342
But you'll still be you.

17:32.593 --> 17:34.303
What's the difference between

17:35.221 --> 17:36.221
being here

17:37.014 --> 17:38.182
and being alive?

17:38.266 --> 17:43.104
Any feeling, sensation, emotion,

17:43.187 --> 17:44.939
much less intense here.

17:45.022 --> 17:46.649
How can you be so sure of that?

17:47.483 --> 17:50.486
Because of a previous experience
as a living person.

17:52.196 --> 17:53.196
So you were picked.

17:54.323 --> 17:56.284
You sat where I sat, and you won.

18:00.997 --> 18:03.791
And what did you achieve
as a living person?

18:06.961 --> 18:10.339
Unfortunately I can't answer
any questions on the subject.

18:11.882 --> 18:13.050
Okay.

18:14.552 --> 18:18.514
I have a task for you.

18:20.766 --> 18:23.519
No right or wrong answer.

18:25.479 --> 18:27.732
Just say whatever comes to mind.

18:34.447 --> 18:35.656
You gonna sit there?

18:35.740 --> 18:38.492
From here on, you're not Anne anymore.

18:40.077 --> 18:44.373
You are a war prisoner
in a concentration camp.

18:44.457 --> 18:48.836
You were sent here yesterday
with your 11-year-old son, Nick.

18:48.919 --> 18:51.714
Very smart boy, but quite rebellious too.

18:52.506 --> 18:55.635
This morning, Nick tried to escape,

18:55.718 --> 18:57.803
but was caught by a sadistic guard

18:57.887 --> 19:00.264
who wants to hang him.

19:00.348 --> 19:01.348
Nick is right here...

19:03.267 --> 19:04.644
Standing on this chair,

19:05.311 --> 19:06.646
with a cord...

19:08.189 --> 19:09.482
Around his neck.

19:10.149 --> 19:13.611
This small piece of furniture
is the only thing preventing

19:13.694 --> 19:15.780
your beloved son from being killed,

19:16.489 --> 19:19.950
when the guard says, "pull the chair."

19:22.370 --> 19:23.371
Pull the chair.

19:23.454 --> 19:25.122
Pull the chair. Pull the chair.

19:25.206 --> 19:26.666
My god.

19:27.917 --> 19:29.293
If you don't pull this chair,

19:30.044 --> 19:32.922
not only will I kill your son,

19:33.005 --> 19:35.341
I'll kill everyone else here.

19:35.424 --> 19:36.509
Shit.

19:48.521 --> 19:50.439
Would you pull the chair or not?

19:52.942 --> 19:54.902
No right or wrong answers.

19:54.985 --> 19:57.530
Just say whatever comes to mind.

20:01.909 --> 20:02.909
Anne.

20:07.832 --> 20:10.000
I wouldn't pull the chair.

20:10.084 --> 20:11.293
Can you tell me why?

20:11.961 --> 20:15.297
Well, if I pull the chair,
my son will die for sure.

20:16.674 --> 20:19.343
But if I don't, there's always
a chance the guard is bluffing.

20:19.427 --> 20:20.803
I would pull the chair.

20:20.886 --> 20:21.886
Why?

20:22.596 --> 20:23.848
Because I don't care.

20:23.931 --> 20:26.767
It's my fault that my son tried to escape,

20:26.851 --> 20:30.604
so it wouldn't be fair
if everyone else died because of us.

20:33.399 --> 20:34.942
I mean, do I have another kid?

20:36.986 --> 20:38.279
I'd attack the guard.

20:38.362 --> 20:41.574
I'm not sure
if you understand the concept of firearms,

20:41.657 --> 20:43.701
but attacking the guard
is a losing battle.

20:43.784 --> 20:45.286
Losing battle like what?

20:46.245 --> 20:49.957
Like attacking a bear
with nothing but your hands.

20:51.333 --> 20:54.170
What makes you so sure
I would lose that fight?

20:54.253 --> 20:56.422
Thank you for sharing that with me, Anne.

20:57.882 --> 21:00.176
I think I have everything I need.

21:00.259 --> 21:01.927
I think I have everything I need.

21:03.429 --> 21:04.638
Thank you.

21:05.639 --> 21:06.724
You're welcome.

21:06.807 --> 21:07.892
Thank you.

21:07.975 --> 21:09.351
Oh, thank you.

21:09.435 --> 21:11.395
- I should go.
- Thank you.

21:13.189 --> 21:14.189
I will go.

21:14.732 --> 21:16.817
Unless you want me...
Unless you have more ques...

21:16.901 --> 21:18.486
Nope? All right.

21:20.738 --> 21:22.364
- Other door.
- Yup.

21:22.448 --> 21:23.448
Sorry.

21:23.824 --> 21:25.910
Still learning the lay of the land.

22:20.297 --> 22:21.382
Got any tea left?

22:23.509 --> 22:25.344
You just enter the house now.

22:25.427 --> 22:28.472
I can never resist a brew.

22:28.556 --> 22:30.266
There's some tea in the kitchen.

22:32.434 --> 22:33.727
Got to get back to work.

22:33.811 --> 22:34.812
Be my guest.

22:35.813 --> 22:39.692
Oh, yeah,
Daniel's got his head deep in pizza.

22:39.775 --> 22:41.193
It's his second one.

22:43.070 --> 22:45.739
Jeannine's been on the toilet now
for 25 minutes.

22:45.823 --> 22:48.325
She should've never had
the shoyu chicken, you know.

22:54.665 --> 22:55.666
You not gonna get that?

22:56.542 --> 22:58.586
Everyone else came on time.

23:12.808 --> 23:14.059
Please, come in.

23:14.143 --> 23:15.352
I'm kyo.

23:15.436 --> 23:16.770
Nice to meet you, kyo.

23:16.854 --> 23:18.981
This is the official entrance.

23:21.817 --> 23:22.817
Welcome.

23:23.736 --> 23:24.736
Please, sit.

23:30.367 --> 23:33.704
This is kyo. He'll be helping me tonight.

23:33.787 --> 23:36.165
Yes, we got introduced.

23:36.248 --> 23:37.708
Good. My name is will.

23:37.791 --> 23:39.543
- May I...
- Nice to meet you, will.

23:43.964 --> 23:45.633
May I call you Emma?

23:51.055 --> 23:52.348
Any problem?

23:52.932 --> 23:53.932
Actually...

23:56.352 --> 23:58.729
May I choose something for myself?

23:59.271 --> 24:02.691
It's just temporary.
If you're selected, you get another name.

24:02.775 --> 24:06.487
But if I'm not selected,
then it is the only one I'll ever have.

24:09.198 --> 24:10.783
Pick another name.

24:10.866 --> 24:12.451
Anything you want.

24:16.830 --> 24:17.998
I like Emma.

24:22.378 --> 24:23.879
Emma it is.

24:25.089 --> 24:27.132
Emma, may I take your picture?

24:28.592 --> 24:31.095
That won't be necessary.

24:32.930 --> 24:34.515
Sorry, it's a bit flashy.

24:34.598 --> 24:36.016
Thank you, kyo.

24:36.100 --> 24:37.810
Emma, do you know why you're here?

24:38.852 --> 24:42.648
All right, before we get started,
do you have any questions?

24:42.731 --> 24:44.149
Is kyo your boss?

24:45.025 --> 24:47.403
I've never thought of it that way, but no.

24:48.070 --> 24:49.780
I would not hire will.

24:49.863 --> 24:52.616
- So you're an interviewer too?
- He's not allowed to interview.

24:52.700 --> 24:53.700
Why?

24:54.868 --> 24:56.245
Unfortunately,

24:57.371 --> 24:58.747
I've never been alive.

25:03.168 --> 25:04.461
All right.

25:04.545 --> 25:06.505
I have a task for you.

25:07.256 --> 25:09.091
I'll start a story.

25:09.174 --> 25:10.801
You tell me how it ends.

25:10.884 --> 25:14.930
Just say whatever comes to mind.

25:15.639 --> 25:18.183
Your name is no longer Emma.

25:18.267 --> 25:20.144
You are a prisoner of war.

25:20.227 --> 25:23.188
- What kind of war?
- Just listen.

25:25.274 --> 25:27.943
You were sent to a concentration camp

25:29.111 --> 25:32.156
with your 11-year-old son, Nick.

25:32.239 --> 25:34.908
This morning, Nick tried to escape,

25:34.992 --> 25:38.328
but was caught by a sadistic guard
who wants to hang him.

25:38.871 --> 25:40.414
Nick is on this chair,

25:40.998 --> 25:43.417
with a cord around his neck.

25:44.626 --> 25:47.671
This small piece of furniture
is the only thing keeping your beloved son

25:47.755 --> 25:48.922
from being killed,

25:50.257 --> 25:52.551
when the guard says, "pull the chair."

25:54.595 --> 25:57.306
Pull the chair.

26:02.102 --> 26:04.396
If you don't pull that chair,

26:04.480 --> 26:07.107
not only will I kill your son,

26:07.191 --> 26:08.859
but all the other prisoners here.

26:08.942 --> 26:10.069
Do you want that?

26:16.575 --> 26:17.785
Will, will.

26:20.788 --> 26:21.789
Pull the chair.

26:35.219 --> 26:36.678
What would you do?

26:38.347 --> 26:40.265
I'm afraid I can't answer that question.

26:40.349 --> 26:41.349
Why not?

26:42.476 --> 26:44.895
Well, the way you put it,

26:44.978 --> 26:47.940
the guard is gonna kill my son
no matter what I do.

26:48.899 --> 26:50.275
- Correct?
- Correct.

26:51.360 --> 26:52.360
Why?

26:53.237 --> 26:54.822
Because he is a bad man.

26:54.905 --> 26:55.905
Why?

26:56.323 --> 26:58.242
Because that is the way it is.

26:58.325 --> 27:02.746
Because that's the way the story is,
or because that's the way the world is?

27:07.126 --> 27:09.545
Would you pull the chair or not?

27:11.588 --> 27:15.384
I'm really not sure if I can answer
your question if you don't answer mine.

27:20.097 --> 27:22.599
Interesting interviewing style
you got there.

27:25.227 --> 27:27.479
So, what'd you think of her?

27:27.563 --> 27:29.481
She didn't answer my questions.

27:30.899 --> 27:32.359
How bad is that?

27:32.442 --> 27:34.111
Everyone else answered them.

27:34.194 --> 27:36.405
Maybe she's more unique
than everyone else.

27:36.488 --> 27:39.366
Or maybe she's most likely
to fall on the battlefield.

27:40.117 --> 27:42.995
You always talk as if
you're sending them to war.

27:43.078 --> 27:46.415
You always talk as if
you've been alive to know anything.

27:46.498 --> 27:47.332
Excuse me?

27:47.416 --> 27:48.709
You're excused.

27:50.627 --> 27:53.714
Listen, will,
I'm not gonna argue with you again.

27:54.423 --> 27:56.383
Do whatever you want to yourself.

27:57.092 --> 27:59.261
Cut your dick off
with a plastic knife if you want.

27:59.344 --> 28:01.847
But for the selections, it's my duty

28:01.930 --> 28:04.057
to point out what I saw here, and that...

28:05.100 --> 28:06.268
That was unique.

28:06.351 --> 28:08.145
Thanks for the advice.

28:08.228 --> 28:09.354
Thanks for the tea.

28:50.270 --> 28:52.814
- Hello.
- Welcome back, Alex.

28:53.523 --> 28:54.523
Thank you.

28:55.484 --> 28:57.110
Hey, wonderful.

28:57.194 --> 28:59.905
Congratulations on making it
to the second day.

28:59.988 --> 29:03.242
Thank you. It's a nice surprise. Thanks.

29:03.325 --> 29:06.245
- Let me show you the house.
- Okay, I get the tour.

29:06.328 --> 29:08.580
- Lamp.
- Oh, lamp. Nice.

29:08.664 --> 29:10.165
Hot. Okay.

29:10.999 --> 29:12.584
This is the kitchen.

29:12.668 --> 29:15.254
Oh, wow, look at this.

29:15.337 --> 29:18.257
Very nice.
You like these two colors, don't you?

29:19.675 --> 29:21.802
Feel free to take anything you like.

29:22.970 --> 29:25.097
Careful what you say.
Careful what you say.

29:25.180 --> 29:26.556
Oh, look at these guys.

29:28.308 --> 29:29.601
Wanna show you the bathroom.

29:29.685 --> 29:32.145
Yeah, sure, sure. Yeah, love that.

29:36.316 --> 29:37.316
This...

29:39.111 --> 29:40.529
Is the bathroom.

29:41.363 --> 29:42.363
Hot.

29:42.781 --> 29:43.907
Cold.

29:46.076 --> 29:48.245
May I turn it on?

29:48.328 --> 29:49.328
Sure.

30:04.386 --> 30:06.763
And this is where
you can see through the eyes

30:06.847 --> 30:09.224
of everyone I've previously selected.

30:18.525 --> 30:19.776
What should I do now?

30:19.860 --> 30:20.861
Just watch them.

30:21.862 --> 30:24.072
And anything you like, write it down.

30:28.368 --> 30:29.286
Can I write anything?

30:29.369 --> 30:30.912
Anything you like.

30:33.957 --> 30:34.958
Megan.

30:35.959 --> 30:37.294
Come here, sweetheart.

30:43.884 --> 30:45.093
What about this one?

30:46.553 --> 30:49.389
That's where you want
to be when this process is over.

30:59.733 --> 31:01.068
If you need anything,

31:02.736 --> 31:04.279
I'll be in this room here.

31:06.365 --> 31:07.365
Oh, will?

31:08.075 --> 31:11.244
Yesterday, you said,
I only have nine days.

31:11.328 --> 31:14.581
Did you start counting yesterday,
or did you start counting today?

31:14.664 --> 31:15.707
Yesterday.

31:16.750 --> 31:18.919
But try not to think too much about it.

31:19.920 --> 31:21.046
Oh, okay.

31:33.600 --> 31:34.434
Hey, Rick.

31:34.518 --> 31:35.727
- Come on, guys.
- Oh, man.

31:37.854 --> 31:38.980
Leave me alone.

31:43.485 --> 31:44.611
Come on, dude.

32:08.969 --> 32:10.554
No, it's not that cold.

32:10.637 --> 32:11.637
Oh, my god.

32:54.181 --> 32:55.307
That was good.

32:59.478 --> 33:00.937
Is everything okay here?

33:01.021 --> 33:02.898
Oh, yeah.

33:05.108 --> 33:06.108
What's that?

33:06.651 --> 33:07.736
Oh, it's nothing.

33:10.530 --> 33:11.530
Can I see?

33:12.324 --> 33:14.284
Oh, really, it's not anything.

33:14.367 --> 33:16.495
If it's not anything, let me see it.

33:19.539 --> 33:21.875
It's a work in progress.

33:23.126 --> 33:24.126
Mike.

33:26.296 --> 33:30.008
Okay, but it's not done.
I just started. It's nothing, just...

