46:30.121 --> 46:34.417
they usually yell something out,
so they can hear their voice echoing.

46:34.500 --> 46:35.334
Okay.

46:35.418 --> 46:37.962
I would take a deep breath, and...

46:50.057 --> 46:51.726
You're laughing, Emma.

46:51.809 --> 46:53.561
I'm laughing with you.

46:53.644 --> 46:55.438
You're... oh, laughing with me.

46:57.690 --> 46:59.191
What about you, will?

47:00.693 --> 47:02.069
I've lived before.

47:03.779 --> 47:04.780
I know.

47:06.240 --> 47:07.742
Is there a moment you'd like to...?

47:07.825 --> 47:09.452
There is no moment.

47:10.119 --> 47:11.746
Not a single one?

47:11.829 --> 47:13.289
From your whole life?

47:13.372 --> 47:14.582
Enough.

47:15.916 --> 47:16.959
Why do you say that?

47:18.127 --> 47:19.754
You're the one who's lived. Why say...?

47:19.837 --> 47:20.837
Enough.

47:22.673 --> 47:25.301
Kyo, can you please
help me take this inside?

47:29.847 --> 47:33.851
Does every interviewer do that
for the candidates who get eliminated?

47:33.934 --> 47:35.770
No, only him.

47:37.021 --> 47:38.272
What happened to him?

47:39.565 --> 47:40.775
When he was alive?

47:46.781 --> 47:47.781
Will was...

47:48.824 --> 47:49.824
Special.

47:50.659 --> 47:51.660
Special how?

47:53.412 --> 47:54.412
Too good.

47:55.581 --> 47:56.581
Too kind.

47:57.208 --> 47:58.709
Too sensitive.

48:00.252 --> 48:02.254
But isn't that a good thing?

48:04.548 --> 48:07.802
When I first saw will,
he was still in one of those tvs.

48:09.261 --> 48:12.681
Talented, but struggled his whole life

48:12.765 --> 48:15.101
to fit into a world different from him.

48:15.976 --> 48:17.520
Did have love inside him.

48:18.938 --> 48:19.980
Maybe too much.

48:21.565 --> 48:23.734
Too much love, no one to give it to.

48:27.363 --> 48:28.363
You know,

48:29.657 --> 48:31.534
we can't do a lot from here,
we really can't,

48:31.617 --> 48:34.703
but there were days
I wished I was with him,

48:36.288 --> 48:39.667
just to let him know
he wasn't alone as he thought he was.

49:48.694 --> 49:49.945
It's match point.

49:50.529 --> 49:52.114
Everything in his favor.

49:52.198 --> 49:55.034
One-love, 40-15, his serve.

49:56.410 --> 49:57.411
He hits the ball.

49:57.995 --> 49:58.829
Net.

49:58.913 --> 50:01.332
So he tries again, but more nervous now.

50:02.708 --> 50:04.043
I think,

50:04.835 --> 50:08.172
"he's done it a thousand times.
He'll be all right."

50:09.381 --> 50:10.382
Net.

50:10.466 --> 50:12.092
- Net.
- Oh, come on.

50:12.176 --> 50:13.427
It's all downhill from there.

50:13.511 --> 50:16.013
- So close to winning, but...
- Damn it.

50:18.349 --> 50:20.684
He let his emotions get in the way.

50:20.768 --> 50:23.145
So in that situation, you would do what?

50:25.856 --> 50:27.107
I'd fight through it.

